<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest <span class="blue">[<span class="yellow">1073</span>]</span> is called '<span class="yellow">Scholarly Studies</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">181</span> to <span class="yellow">241</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/3438">Lord Vashir</a> [<a href="/area/61">The Towne of New Rigel</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

I ask that you become a better student and develop your study skills, for<br />
the learned Adventurer is most successful in that which is undertaken.  The<br />
more knowledgeable those in service to me become, the more competent and<br />
well advised their help.  To this end, take up quill and parchment and apply<br />
yourself diligently to your studies.  Visit the great libraries of Sepharia<br />
from north to southernmost, and strive to understand all you can from the<br />
more knowledgeable persons of the land.  I trust that you will take few<br />
liberties with such a pivotal task and will remove any obstacles to your<br />
steady studious progress.  After your studies are complete, return to me and<br />
I shall reward your hard work most handsomely.  May the Powers aid you on<br />
your quest for knowledge!  <br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">60</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">7</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">40,000</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">10,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">200</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Scholarly Studies consists of:<br />


